Plum pox potyvirus, surveillance - Canada 20000812.1339
Plum pox potyvirus, surveillance - Canada (06) 20000921.1631
Date: 22 Nov 2000
From: Dick Hamilton rihamilto@home.com
Source: Canadian Food Inspection Agency, Plum Pox Potyvirus Survey Update,
14 Nov 2000 [edited

The 2000 National PPV survey has now been completed. Sampling was
conducted in Ontario, Quebec, British Columbia, and Nova Scotia.
Additional positive sites [were identified in Ontario in recent weeks, and
one positive sample [was identified in Nova Scotia. No positives were
found in British
Columbia or Quebec.
Samples were tested by the CFIA Centre for Animal and Plant Health in
Charlottetown, P.E.I., in addition to CFIA laboratories in Sidney, B.C. and
Nepean, Ontario. Sample preparation support was provided by laboratories of
Agriculture and Agri-Food Canada in Summerland, British Columbia and
Vineland, Ontario.
As of 14 Nov 2000, the following results were obtained:
Total PPV-susceptible Prunus Samples Collected
Ontario 100 913
British Columbia 9048
Quebec 816
Nova Scotia 1377
Total PPV-susceptible Prunus Samples Tested*
Ontario 101 009
British Columbia 9048
Quebec 816
Nova Scotia 1377
Total PPV-Positive Site Locations
Ontario 57**
British Columbia 0
Quebec 0
Nova Scotia 1***
Total PPV-Positive Samples
Ontario 947
British Columbia 0
Quebec 0
Nova Scotia 1
Total PPV-Negative Samples
Ontario 99 966
British Columbia 9048
Quebec 816
Nova Scotia 1376
*Includes individual, composite, strain typing, replacement and special
request samples.
**53 in the Niagara Peninsula, 2 near Blenheim, 1 near Simcoe, and 1 near
Fonthill
***1 in the Annapolis Valley
