ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[The test method used in the survey was a triple antibody sandwich ELISA
using an anti-PPV polyclonal antiserum for trapping the antigen, a
monoclonal antibody (5B-IVIA, Durviz s.l, Spain) as the secondary antibody
and goat anti-mouse alkaline phosphatase conjugate as the tertiary
antibody. 5B detects all known PPV serotypes including (D [apricot,
France, M [peach, Greece, SP [peach. France, EA [Egypt, and C [sour
cherry, Moldova, a.k.a. SoC) but does not bind to other potyviruses. The
only strain detected in the Canadian survey was the D strain. The disease
seems widely distributed in Ontario and has also been detected in a
confined area in Nova Scotia. The apparent absence of the virus in British
Columbia and Quebec will likely call for continued surveying as part of a
national strategy for managing the disease. - Mod.DH
